The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 31 January is 198,868 (22,920.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 January, there were 11,050 new confirmed cases (1,273.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 January, there were 9,211 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 20% (1,839 extra cases).
